<br>
He had seemed a bit unconventional, to say the least. Instead of wielding magic with the calculating efficiency of Valdayana D`Varr or passionate devotion of Saldaria Snowspirit, Quasqueton blithely hurled lightning or fire at the walking dead or golem sentries that protected the place as if he were playing a game of catch. Eventually they obtained the final piece of armor for his collection, a chainmail tunic. Millikin had been surprised that the enchantment placed on by its iksar creators granting the wearer enhanced strength had remained in tact despite the onslaught of magic and melee required to destroy the iksar skeletal remains that had been wearing it.<br>
<br>
She had met him subsequently a few more times, once in the Umbral Plains, but more commonly in Velious. During a Coldain assault on the Ry`Gorr fort, a gem mining expedition in the Siren's Grotto, and once while exploring the Dragon Necropolis. Millikin snapped out of her mental reverie as Shiobahn explained that they had been married recently.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, I do know him. I've met him and adventured with him, the last time was while in Velious.&quot; Millikin rubbed the back of her neck, idly wondering how such a detail could have been forgotten to have been mentioned by her parents or her sister in their correspondence. Then it occurred to her that even they may not know. Acting on spontaneous impulse was a common trait, particularly in the Goldbrooke family and Millikin could not honestly say she always acted only after careful deliberation.<br>
<br>
Nor could she exactly sum up her feelings on hearing the news except that she somehow expected it to come back and haunt her. Somehow. Millikin reached for the black medicine pouch she was wearing around her neck to make sure it was still there as she downed the last of her wine then took a deep breath, hoping her offer wouldn't turn out to be more than she bargained for.<br>
<br>
&quot;It appears my list of errands for arcanists is expanding. Did you have a message you wanted me to deliver to him?&quot; <br>
